You have an exact duplicate on the time columns in your data.  That really throws things off.  So, the first thing to do is to introduce a unique number.  In this case, it uses `row_number()`:

    select a.*,
           sum(case when prev_testid = testid then 0 else 1 end) over (partition by id order by [from], seqnum) as calculated_valued
    from (select a.*,
                 lag(testid) over (partition by id order by [from], seqnum) as prev_testid
          from (select a.*, row_number() over (partition by id order by [from], [until], testid) as seqnum
                from @testTab a
               ) a
         ) a
    order by a.[From];

However, I would recommend including an `identity` column in the table and using that, as in [this db&lt;&gt;fiddle][1].


