You can set `nativeQuery = true` in the `@Query` annotation from a `Repository` class like this:

    public static final String FIND_PROJECTS = &quot;SELECT projectId, projectName FROM projects&quot;;
    
    @Query(value = FIND_PROJECTS, nativeQuery = true)
    public List&lt;Object[]&gt; findProjects();


It&#39;s probably worth looking at the Spring data [docs][1] as well.

***Some more example*** 
***1.*** 

    public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository&lt;User, Long&gt; {
    
      @Query(value = &quot;SELECT * FROM USERS WHERE EMAIL_ADDRESS = ?1&quot;, nativeQuery = true)
      User findByEmailAddress(String emailAddress);
    }



  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-data/jpa/docs/current/reference/html/#jpa.query-methods.at-query

